issues.body:
For some reason between 3.48 and 3.50 presigned URLs for uploading/PutObject are totally broken.

I get this error: `The request signature we calculated does not match the signature you provided. Check your key and signing method.`.

The key is fine and the signing method is fine. Zero code issues. How do I know this? Because it worked in 3.48 and the same code still generates valid presigned GetObject URLs.

Code that generates:

```php
       /**
     * Handles the request based on the given method
     *
     * @param string $objectKey The object key for the request
     * @param string $method    The method used in the request command
     *
     * @return string
     */
    private function handler(string $objectKey, string $method)
    {
        $bucket = $this->adapter->getBucket();

        $s3Cmd = $this->client->getCommand($method, [
            'Bucket' => $bucket,
            'Key'    => $objectKey,
        ]);

        $expiry = env('MEDIA_API_EXPIRY_TIME_SECONDS') ?: self::SIGNED_TIME_IN_SECONDS;

        $s3Request = $this->client->createPresignedRequest($s3Cmd, '+' . $expiry . ' seconds');

        return $s3Request->getUri()->__toString();
    }
```
`$method` is either "GetObject" or "PutObject":

```php
   /**
     * Creates a pre-signed URL to download/access a file that will expire after a given time
     *
     * @param string $objectKey The object key of the file that will be downloaded
     *
     * @return string
     */
    public function download(string $objectKey)
    {
        return $this->handler($objectKey, self::GET_OBJECT);
    }

    /**
     * Creates a pre-signed URL to upload a file that will expire after a given time
     *
     * @param string $objectKey The object key of the file that will be uploaded
     *
     * @return string
     */
    public function upload(string $objectKey)
    {
        return $this->handler($objectKey, self::PUT_OBJECT);
    }
```

Spent a couple of hours with this before realising the PHP AWS SDK library updated two days ago and now this is broken, so I suspect they're related.

For brevity, the constants:

```php
    const GET_OBJECT = "GetObject";
    const PUT_OBJECT = "PutObject";
    const SIGNED_TIME_IN_SECONDS = 300;
```

