I did some refactoring to Guzzle (the underlying framework of the SDK), and I've corrected this issue. The problem was that there was a circular reference of a request to a response that was causing the request to and it's associated objects to have a refcount > 0, so they only get cleaned up when the garbage collection runs (cleaning up circular references like this). You can update to the dev-master version of Guzzle to get this change.

In the meantime, I suggest that you close the file yourself when you're done with it to ensure that memory and resources are managed in a way suitable to your use case.

